              "id": "fn-resurrection-ascension-135",
              "number": 135,
              "content": "&nbsp;The spread of sound Islamic religion that accurately represents the Prophet globally and in other faith communities is also one of the Signs of the End of Time. It will happen most thoroughly after the Second Coming of Jesus Christ, when Jews and Christians will convert. It is also three times indicated in the Qur’ān that God would render the religion of His last Prophet uppermost over all other faith communities, which is something that began to happen effectively during the Prophet’s lifetime and in all subsequent generations. Islam has always been successful at spreading in all other faith communities and cultures throughout the world, once it is well established and becomes known. God says in the Qur’ān: “He it is Who sent His Messenger with guidance and the religion of truth to make it prevail over all relgion, though the idolaters be averse” (The Ranks, 61:9; see also 9:33; 48:28). In these verses, “all religion” means “all other religions” or, more specifically, “the people of all other religions.” Likewise, God willed that the Muslim Community be sound, intelligent, and upright so that it serve as a witness over all humanity, which has a closely related meaning. God says in the Qur’ān: “Thus, did We make you a middle Community so that you be witnesses over mankind and so that the Messenger be a witness over you” (The Cow, 2:143; see also 22:78). Some commentators relate these verses directly to the coming of the Mahdī and the Second Coming of Jesus Christ. This complements the notion that the world Community of Islam was put on earth to be “witnesses over mankind,” meaning that their faith and justice will be witnessed by humanity as evidence of the truth of religion. Ultimately, no aspect of the “Religion of Truth” will remain hidden.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br/>",
